description.narrative: (Vietnam): The Partner Capacity Development (PCD) Program provides technical assistance interventions designed to increase the performance and sustainability of Vietnamese non-governmental organizations and government institutions to support USAID/Vietnam Country Development Cooperation Strategy. Activities are aimed at improving the internal operation of these organizations, such as, financial management, strategic planning and performance measurement, leadership, and HR policies...With FY 2017 funds, PCD will continue to provide interventions (training sessions, workshops) to local organizations to address root causes of poor performance. It will also support efforts to integrate training and capacity building assistance into USAID/Vietnam's strategic priorities, including study tours, policy workshops, and others. The program provides participant training services for academic education and technical training of professionals for both public and private institutions.
